      <div align="justify">
				
Jason Thorpe Buchanan is an American composer, Artistic Director of <a href="http://www.switchensemble.com" target="_blank">the [Switch~ Ensemble]</a>, Executive Director of the <a href="http://www.vipafestival.org" target="_blank">Valencia International Performance Academy & Festival (Spain)</a>, and Curator for the <a href="http://centerfornewmusic.com/" target="_blank">San Francisco Center for New Music</a>.
Commissioned and performed internationally by ensembles such as <a href="www.alarmwillsound.com" target="_blank">Alarm Will Sound</a> (USA), <a href="http://taleaensemble.org/" target="_blank">Talea</a> (USA), <a href="http://www.ensembleinterface.com/" target="_blank">Interface</a> (DE), <a href="http://www.ensemblenikel.com/" target="_blank"> Nikel</a> (Israel), <a href="http://www.ensemble-linea.com/" target="_blank">Linea</a> (FR), Insomnio (NL), EXAUDI (UK), Slagwerk Den Haag (NL), Eklekto Percussion (CH), <a href "http://www.mivosquartet.com/" target="_blank">Mivos Quartet</a> (USA), <a href="http://www.iktuspercussion.com" target="_blank">Iktus Percussion</a>, <a href="http://theindustryla.org" target="_blank">The Industry</a>, <a href="http://wildup.la" target="_blank">wild Up</a>, F&#220;NF&#43;F&#220;NF Festival (DE), and the <a href="http://www.esm.rochester.edu/ensembles/musicanova/" target="_blank">Eastman Musica Nova Ensemble</a>, among others.
Scenes from <a href="http://www.hungeropera.com" target="_blank"><em>Hunger</em></a> have received performances at Darmstadt, <a href="http://theindustryla.org" target="_blank">The Industry</a>'s FIRST TAKE in L.A., and <a href="http://matafestival.org/mata-interval/" target="_blank">MATA</a> in NYC with <a href="http://www.switchensemble.com" target="_blank">the [Switch~ Ensemble]</a>.

&nbsp; &nbsp; Honors include a Fulbright Fellowship, nomination for the 2015 Gaudeamus Prize, commissions from Royaumont (2016 & 17), AiR USF Verftet (Norway), American-Scandinavian Foundation Grant, ASCAP Morton Gould Award (2014-15), Howard Hanson Orchestral Prize, and winner of Iron Composer.
He has served as instructor in electronic music/composition and assistant conductor for the Musica Nova Ensemble with <a href="http://bradlubman.me/" target="_blank">Brad Lubman</a> as a Ph.D. candidate at the Eastman School of Music, and as a guest at Chamber Music Campania (Italy), SJSU, UNLV, QNMF, MATA, Portland State University, University of Richmond, UNCG, MSU, BEK (Norway), and at the University of Chicago in a residency with the [Switch~ Ensemble] (2017).
Current projects include <a href="http://www.hungeropera.com/" target="_blank"><em>Hunger</em></a> and commissions from <a href="https://www.royaumont.com/fr/programme-voix-nouvelles" target="_blank">Royaumont Acad&eacute;mie Voix Nouvelles Ensemble</a> (France, Sep.2017), the Earle Brown Music Foundation for <a href="http://taleaensemble.org/" target="_blank">Talea Ensemble</a>/Time Spans Festival (NYC, Aug.2017), and <a href="http://5plus5-festival.de/" target="_blank">F&#220;NF&#43;F&#220;NF Contrabass Clarinet and Percussion Festival</a> in Berlin (Germany, 2018).
